Title: Mcqs In Human Physiology Basic And Applied
Author: ও পি ট্যান্ডন
Summary:
"Mcqs In Human Physiology Basic And Applied" Summary Of The Book:
Among the highlights of this fourth edition of MCQs in Human Physiology is the further addition of about 500 important questions in order to catch up with the enormously expanding knowledge of human physiology and its allied fields. The present edition offers an excellent review and compilation of over 2,000 different types of MCQs including problem-based exercises, based on concepts and fundamentals involved in understanding of the subject. Effort has been made to refer to standard textbooks and Guyton's Textbook have been cited quite often for ready reference.
This edition will help the students, both at undergraduate and postgraduate levels for their competitive and medical entrance exams, including those appearing for Civil Service Examination with special paper in medical sciences. Besides, this book will also be very useful for students appearing in MBBS, BDS, B
